      "id": 1,
      "text": "Sweetwater Marina & Riverdeck now occupies the 1924 Sweetwater Casino site, a historic riverside spot on the Mullica River.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://sweetwaterriverdeck.com/our-story/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Despite its name, the original Sweetwater Casino never housed a gambling hall; it operated as a prohibition-era speakeasy.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4,
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://sweetwaterriverdeck.com/our-story/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The community lies on the Mullica River, roughly 20 miles from Atlantic City.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sweetwater%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "A lightning‑strike fire in 2008 destroyed the Sweetwater Casino, a loss remembered by locals.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
